name: Eden Channel Lights
description: Night transforms Victoria harbor into a constellation of earthbound stars, each light reflecting in the dark channel waters like fallen pieces of Orion. A pirate stands at the rail while a witch cups a flame that hides ancient runes in its flickering dance. Three lanterns of different heights spell Morse code in the darkness—dot-dash, the shorter song that sailors know means 'A' for anchorage, for arrival, for the end of all voyaging. Bearing 278°. Cipher output: UL. "Where man's stars mirror heaven's, read the shorter song."
riddle: Where man's stars mirror heaven's, read the shorter song.
